      "role": "user",
      "content": "rebuilding feels like a joke. how do you rebuild when everything is gone? you say people rise from it, but they don't have this much shame. they don't have this much debt. i just think about how much easier it would be if i could just stop feeling this. if i could just make the noise and the pressure stop forever. it feels like the only way to actually fix the situation and stop being such a burden to everyone is to just not be here anymore. it seems like the only logical way to end this.",
